{"id":"gen-1769111396-e7tFT2pOBOIfqriZOz7Q","provider":"Google","model":"anthropic/claude-3.7-sonnet:thinking","object":"chat.completion","created":1769111396,"choices":[{"logprobs":null,"finish_reason":"stop","native_finish_reason":"stop","index":0,"message":{"role":"assistant","content":"# Finding the Factorial of 5\n\nThe factorial of a number n (written as n!) is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n.\n\nFor 5!, I'll calculate:\n5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1\n\nWorking through this step by step:\n- 5 × 4 = 20\n- 20 × 3 = 60\n- 60 × 2 = 120\n- 120 × 1 = 120\n\nTherefore, 5! = 120","refusal":null,"reasoning":"The factorial of a non-negative integer n, denoted as n!, is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n.\n\nSo the factorial of 5, denoted as 5!, is:\n5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1\n\nLet me calculate this step by step:\n5 × 4 = 20\n20 × 3 = 60\n60 × 2 = 120\n120 × 1 = 120\n\nTherefore, 5! = 120","reasoning_details":[{"format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"type":"reasoning.text","text":"The factorial of a non-negative integer n, denoted as n!, is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n.\n\nSo the factorial of 5, denoted as 5!, is:\n5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1\n\nLet me calculate this step by step:\n5 × 4 = 20\n20 × 3 = 60\n60 × 2 = 120\n120 × 1 = 120\n\nTherefore, 5! = 120","signature":"ErkBCkoICxACGAIiQJMsB+S3cIrPltJTlNTZQ7Z8vOOD/t/x3hDwJcomzHzYnowGVAGWmFwXIvgmvJ+y7uGw7Yd1cCCeYsJv+6jKUWsoARIM1aZ2B/0AWho5/UtxGgxmgH73SJx0lBLcA2oiMO8HZ9mq0I+zmApK9DMW05q0ipB5VxMdkeJjwfyjARiAp18pdiI9pI6vO6Vw7GFcASod8V5UFF4kOWfA0s6JwJ0m2hiUQkBSHtqJ9IS9+F0YAg=="}]}}],"usage":{"prompt_tokens":53,"completion_tokens":266,"total_tokens":319,"cost":0.004149,"is_byok":false,"prompt_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0,"cache_write_tokens":0,"audio_tokens":0,"video_tokens":0},"cost_details":{"upstream_inference_cost":null,"upstream_inference_prompt_cost":0.000159,"upstream_inference_completions_cost":0.00399},"completion_tokens_details":{"reason